  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing Agriculture, Livestock, and Livelihood Support Program in North Darfur</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Line ministries continue to be unable to assume full responsibility for meeting these needs in these rural areas, having no management and operations funding outside the complimentary support RI can bring in, and without this relief the livestock and self-generated farming food security will continue to decline into further crisis. RI&apos;s proposed program is designed to provide immediate inputs via seeds and tools distribution and livestock health care, while concurrently conducting training programs for lasting impact. With ongoing oversight by RI and continued emergency inputs, ministry, community leaders and RI-trained veterinary and agriculture community teams will serve as the key participatory actors and oversight for fostering growth in local resources. Supported and conducted in coordination with the MoA and MoAR, farmers are beginning to change behaviors from subsistence to food secure strategies. RI&apos;s methodology for agriculture and food security interventions seeks to advance villages beyond the current fragile subsistence state that makes them unable to rebound from conflict disaster, economic downturns, or environmental fluctuations, which takes time and several cycles of support.</narrative>
  </description>
